==English==
===Etymology===
*Thought to allude to the former practice of binding government documents in red-coloured tape
===Noun phrase===
[[Category:English idioms]]
'''red tape'''
#a [[derisive]] term for [[regulation]]s or [[bureaucratic]] procedures that are considered [[excess]]ive or excessively time- and effort-consuming
#:''All the red tape and paperwork that goes on there prevents any progress.''
 
